DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "contextFiniteSolutionSets.pl", "contextForm.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context("FiniteSolutionSets"); $answer = Formula("{-55/3}");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Solve the equation [`-\frac{3}{5}x=11`] for [`x\text{.}`]
[_]{$answer}{10}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION Our variable [`x`] is multiplied by the fraction [`-\frac{3}{5}\text{.}`] This is a negative number, so we should multiply by something negative to undo that part. But also we should multiply by the reciprocal of [`\frac{3}{5}\text{,}`] which is [`\frac{5}{3}\text{.}`] All together, we should multiply each side by [`-\frac{5}{3}\text{.}`]
[```\newcommand{\highlight}[1]{\mathchoice{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\displaystyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\textstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptscriptstyle #1$}}}\newcommand{\multiplyleft}[2][\cdot]{{\highlight{{#2#1{}}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} -\frac{3}{5}x\amp=11\\ \multiplyleft{-\frac{5}{3}}\left(-\frac{3}{5}x\right)\amp=\multiplyleft{-\frac{5}{3}}(11)\\ 1x\amp=-\frac{5}{3}\left(\highlight{\frac{11}{1}}\right)\\ x\amp=-\frac{55}{3} \end{aligned} ```]
We should check the solution by substituting [`-\frac{55}{3}`] in for [`x`] in the original equation:
[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\confirm}[1]{\stackrel{\checkmark}{#1}}\newcommand{\wonder}[1]{\stackrel{\text{?}}{#1}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} -\frac{3}{5}\substitute{\left(-\frac{55}{3}\right)}\amp\wonder{=}11\\ -\frac{\cancel{3}}{5}\left(-\frac{55}{\cancel{3}}\right)\amp\wonder{=}11\\ -\frac{1}{5}\left(-\frac{55}{1}\right)\amp\wonder{=}11\\ \frac{55}{5}\amp\confirm{=}11 \end{aligned} ```]
The solution [`-\frac{55}{3}`] is checked, and the solution set is [`\left\{-\frac{55}{3}\right\}\text{.}`]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
